Definition: excessively unwilling to spend
Example: parsimonious thrift relieved by few generous impulses; lived in a most penurious manner--denying himself every indulgence
Synonyms: noun, attribute, parsimony, parsimoniousness, penurious, penuriousness, excessively, unwilling, to, spend, thrift, relieved, by, few, generous, impulses, lived, in, a, most, manner--denying, himself, every, indulgence
Category: adj.all
